# 1Password secret references for OpenClaw
#
# This file maps environment variables to 1Password items using op:// URIs.
# Copy to ~/.config/op/env on the Pi and uncomment the lines you need.
#
# Format: VAR_NAME=op://<vault>/<item>/<field>
#
# Two vaults:
#   openclaw_read  — credentials YOU set up (API keys, tokens)
#   openclaw_write — items the BOT manages (it can store/retrieve)
#
# The systemd service uses `op run --env-file` to resolve these at startup.
# Secrets are injected into the process environment — never written to disk.
#
# NOTE: If using google-gemini-cli as your LLM provider (recommended),
# no LLM API key is needed here — Gemini CLI uses OAuth (run `gemini` to authenticate).
# The Required section below is empty unless you use an API-key-based LLM provider.

# ── Required ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# (empty — google-gemini-cli uses OAuth, not an API key)

# ── Optional — uncomment as you add services ─────────────────────────
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=op://openclaw_read/anthropic-api-key/credential
# BRAVE_API_KEY=op://openclaw_read/brave-search/credential
# TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=op://openclaw_read/twilio/account-sid
# TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=op://openclaw_read/twilio/auth-token
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=op://openclaw_read/telegram-bot/token
# OPENAI_API_KEY=op://openclaw_read/openai-api-key/credential
